

a) Download version / install sources

cd $LOCAL_BASE (/usr/local/swissbib)
wget http://mirror.switch.ch/mirror/apache/dist/lucene/solr/5.2.1/solr-5.2.1.tgz
tar xfz solr-5.2.1.tgz
ln -s solr-5.2.1.tgz solr
cd $SOLR_BASE (/usr/local/swissbib/solr)

cp start.sh $SOLR_BASE
cp stop.sh $SOLR_BASE

b) create sb-biblio core

mkdir /swissbib_index/solrIndexBiblio

scp -r sb-biblio.core/logs [user]@host:/swissbib_index/solrIndexBiblio
scp -r sb-biblio.core/solr [user]@host:/swissbib_index/solrIndexBiblio



c) Starten des servers
cd $SOLR_BASE
./start.sh

d) stop des servers
cd $SOLR_BASE
./stop.sh

obviously you can use the commands in the shell utilities directly by yourself



e) to index some testdata on sb-s1.swissbib.unibas.ch for SOLR 5.2.1
cd $SOLR_MAR/dist
./sb_post2solr_localhost.sh
(ths is only a test utility to index on localhost and to prevent unintended indexing on other hosts -especially productive ones-)










